  "summary": "forge-jsxy@1.0.104: multiple suspicious patterns require human review",
  "details": "Package contains a postinstall script (scripts/postinstall-agent.mjs) and several files exhibiting patterns commonly associated with supply-chain risk: base64 buffer decoding in deploymentDefaults.js, hfCredentials.js, contentScanner.js, and scripts/encode-deployment.mjs; ping/POST shell-and-network co-occurrence in discordRelayUpload.js, relayServer.js, and the postinstall script; and hardcoded fetch() calls to huggingface.co in secretScan/agentStartupAudit.js. The huggingface.co destination is plausible for a package whose names reference HF credentials and secret scanning, but the combination of a postinstall agent script, base64 decoding routines, and network primitives warrants manual inspection of the postinstall script's behavior, the deploymentDefaults base64 blobs, and the discordRelayUpload module before the package can be confidently allowed or blocked.",
